timing_sdf_adj...tive_setuphold(25.10)  timing_sdf_adj...tive_setuphold(25.10)

Name
       timing_sdf_adjust_negative_setuphold

Syntax
       timing_sdf_adjust_negative_setuphold

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Controls how the setup and hold check values are adjusted when both are
       initially negative in the SDF file.

       When  set to true, the software sets the smaller check delay value to a
       negated  larger  check  delay  value.  For  example,  if  the   initial
       setup/hold value is equal to -1/-2. then the value -2 from the setup is
       smaller  and  it is reset to a negated value of the larger one (-1 from
       hold). So the adjusted setup/hold value is equal to -1/1.

       When set to false, both the negative setup and hold  check  values  are
       set to 0.

       The command order for using this global variable is as follows:

              * read_sdf

              * timing_sdf_adjust_negative_setuphold {true | false}

              * write_sdf

       The timing report (report_timing) results are not impacted.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

